metadata.name: Tesseract #178
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.name: Pebbles #47
metadata.description:
Generative series in six different ranges of 30 colors each that are combined with 150 colors forming a wall. "The Pebbles" series pays tribute to these first ancestral wall constructions in dry stone without concrete to hold them together. It is an ancient technique that dates back to the Stone Age.

This series of generatives NFTs is born from the drawings presented in Milan at the Galería Patricia Armocida. They are composed of stone blocks in 6 series of 50 originals in which 30 colors per range are combined with 150 secondary range colors in infinite shapes.

http://www.nuriamora.com/serie-piedras/

The first Range is Blue.


Coded in P5js.

Source code based on Roni Kaufman previous work and used under a collaborative agreement.

metadata.name: Face Hotel #103
metadata.description:
Face hotel is a digital and artistic version of the insect hotels we see while walking in parks.
This project is the result of a 4-hands work by visual artist Guillaumit and coder and musician Morusque.
For many years Guillaumit has been developing a work based on geometrical shapes combined in a personal way with delicate illustrative elements that seem to give his compositions a soul.
After having designed giant art projects in public spaces for collaborative frescoes Guillaumit decided to work in the world of generative art with the same concern of sincerity and singularity.
This canvas is fully generative and doesn't use predefined graphical assets. It has been designed to be viewed in 800x800, press ENTER to save a screenshot or ALT to save a 5x bigger picture.

metadata.name: Balloonz #61
metadata.description:
3d scene with animated interactive camera

Who among us did not dream of becoming a real aeronaut as a child?
An exciting experience of overcoming gravity only by heating the air!
An endless moment of flight, joy and delight!

- random number ot Balloonz 3-7;
- random arrangement of Balloonz in space;
- 20 coloring patterns;
- 4 algorithms for generating palettes, based on the HSL model;
- 9 skyboxes with different locations, weather and time of day;
- free camera - you can move, rotate, change focal length,
as you like to achieve visual pleasure!

It is recommended to look at the full screen.


[Mouse Click] - Pause/Play
[Left Mouse Button + Move] - Сamera Rotate
[Right Mouse Button + Move] - Сamera Move
[Rotate Mouse Wheel] or [Middle Mouse Button + Move] - Сamera Zoom
[+ -] - Change Сamera Focal Length

Implemented using Three JS

metadata.name: Primitifs systématiques #146
metadata.description:
Primitifs systématiques is the first generative instalment of David Umemoto’s studies of space and volume. Placed at the crux of brutalism and minimalism, these structures based on the original stackable concrete piece Primitif 04 evoke impossible paths yet to be explored. 

The original Primitif 04 has been both preserved and dented, conserved and enhanced. It is still here. But it cannot be found, only encountered. Throughout your explorations of the Primitifs systématiques, you will find that its original shapes have been multiplied, rotated, re-ordered to create new structures. After spending some time exploring its paths, when you stop looking for it, you will realize that 04 is still here, intact.

Lines of work chosen for this piece also draw a perspective. The orientation of the primitives pulls directly towards an intense source of light. Sometimes it is visible, sometimes it is not. This perfect alignment is a call to life. They who look at the sunrise with relief cannot be anything but hopeful. But how can we project life on a concrete behemoth? Stand long enough in front of it, and you too will see that we have no choice but to.

----

Primitifs systématiques is the generative art genesis piece of David Umemoto. It was built in collaboration with Anaglyphic. It is the first collaborative spatial token made available on the anaver.se.
